Watching in July but this video has earned a slot in my favorite practices; perfectly balanced and light-hearted. I have a request (if we are still doing requests in these virus hiatus times): a practice for dissociation/depersonalization. I've been struggling tirelessly with episodes of dissociation that now accompany my general anxiety -- which has been turned on to turbo drive in recent months. I am fortunate enough to have access to mental health professionals and I've learned to use meditation and yoga to curb those feelings of reality/bodily detachment. Sometimes, however, when I turn to yoga in those episodes, I wrestle to stay focused, present, and grounded. This practice and the new "Shift" video have been the most helpful and I have created a routine from them but having a guide during depersonalized panic attacks is endlessly helpful -- I feel safer and less alone. Nonetheless, I can't thank you enough for giving us the gift of at home practice <3
